HEADWORD: Broadbrim
<hw>Broad"brim`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
hat with a very broad brim, like those worn by men of the society of
Friends.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A member of the society of Friends; a Quaker.</def>
<mark>[Sportive]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Broad-brimmed</ent>⟦br⟧
